title: Campus Sustainability Project
description: Help make our campus more environmentally friendly by promoting recycling, energy conservation, and sustainable food options.

title: Peer Tutoring Program
description: Provide free tutoring to fellow students struggling in math, science, writing, or other subjects.

title: Coding Workshops
description: Host free workshops to teach other students coding skills like Python, JavaScript, and web development.

title: Community Garden
description: Start a community garden to grow fresh produce for students and donate surplus to food banks.

title: Student-Athlete Mentoring
description: Mentor local youth athletes to develop skills and character through sports.

title: Homelessness Outreach
description: Provide support for the local homeless population through donations, meals, and other assistance.

title: STEM Education Outreach
description: Inspire youth to pursue careers in science and tech through hands-on activities and mentorship.

title: Student Film Festival
description: Showcase student films and provide opportunities for feedback and recognition.

title: Mental Health Awareness
description: Promote mental health awareness through campus events, peer counseling, and reducing stigma.

title: Blood Drive
description: Organize blood donation drives to support local hospitals and save lives.

title: Cultural Exchange Events
description: Foster cultural understanding between students through food festivals, exhibits and sharing traditions.

title: Student Newspaper
description: Give students journalism experience by starting a campus newspaper.

title: Study Abroad Ambassador Program
description: Support future study abroad students with advice and resources from student ambassadors.

title: Career Mentor Network
description: Connect students to alumni mentors in their desired careers for advice and networking.

title: Student Feedback Forum
description: Provide a way for students to give anonymous feedback to improve campus policies and facilities.
